# PortBay Community — example environment overrides.
#
# PortBay Community needs NO secrets, API keys, or tokens to build or run. It is
# a local-first tool; the only cloud endpoint it knows is the PUBLIC PortBay
# Cloud API, hard-coded as a default. Everything below is an OPTIONAL developer
# override with a safe placeholder value. Copy to `.env` only if you need one.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` is gitignored. Never put real secrets here — proprietary Cloud/Pro
# configuration lives in the private portbay-cloud repository, not this one.

# Rust log filter for the core/daemon (see the `tracing`/`env_logger` syntax).
# RUST_LOG=info,portbay=debug

# Override the bundled Process Compose admin port (default is chosen at runtime).
# PORTBAY_PC_PORT=8765

# Extra directory scanned for project app definitions (testing / multi-root dev).
# PORTBAY_EXTRA_APP_DIR=/absolute/path/to/extra/apps

# Restrict which MCP toolsets the `portbay-mcp` binary exposes (comma-separated).
# PORTBAY_MCP_TOOLSETS=projects,lifecycle

# Opt-in telemetry endpoint override. Empty/unset disables remote telemetry.
# This is a PUBLIC ingest URL, never a secret. Crash/usage data is opt-in only.
# PORTBAY_TELEMETRY_ENDPOINT=https://telemetry.portbay.app/ingest
